    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This is the expected behavior.  See the [Defined Levels](https://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/advanced.html#defined-levels) section of the docs, in particular the [`remove_unused_levels`](https://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/generated/pandas.MultiIndex.remove_unused_levels.html) method achieves what you want.\r\n\r\n> Please note this transpired because I cannot figure out how to get the bounds of the first level of the index (ie: start and end date) other than through df.index.levels[0] - how can I do that?\r\n\r\nNot exactly sure what you mean by this, or what (if any) underlying assumptions there are about the data in the index.  This is probably better suited for StackOverflow, but perhaps you're looking for one of the following: \r\n  - `df.index.get_level_values(0)`\r\n  - `df.index.unique(level=0)`\r\n  - `df.index[0][0]`/`df.index[-1][0]`\r\n  - `df.index.min()[0]`/`df.index.max()[0]`\r\n"
  },
